    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-25T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-25T01:00:00-05:00" n="1137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.351/10–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-25T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 25, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 25—4:42 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1323. From Paddock: Reference last paragraph Deptel 898, October 24 to
                        Seoul.<note n="85" xml:id="d1137fn85">Not printed.</note> I sent plain
                    language telegram October 21 from Dairen through usual Soviet Consulate General
                    channel, saying we embarking that day. Soon as ship left harbor, I sent telegram
                    to American Embassy, Seoul, to relay to Department (radio operator said this
                    fastest method) stating we had embarked without difficulties and requesting
                    Department notify interested posts Consulate closed as of October 21. Now find
                    Embassy never received this telegram. [Paddock.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
